-- Russia Submits Draft Resolution on Syria Monitoring Team
-- B y   A n n a   S h i r y a e v s k a y a
-- 2012-04-20T17:32:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-20/russia-submits-draft-resolution-on-syria-monitoring-team.html
Russia submitted a draft resolution
to the  United Nations Security Council  on setting up a UN
monitoring mission in  Syria , the Foreign Ministry said in a
 statement  on its website today.  The document proposes a UN mission of 300 observers for an
initial period of 90 days, Alexander Lukashevich, a spokesman
for the Foreign Ministry in Moscow, said in the statement.  A decision on the Russian draft may be made as soon as
tomorrow, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anna Shiryaevskaya in Moscow at 
 ashiryaevska@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Kennedy at 
 wkennedy3@bloomberg.net  